<p><i>Ryse: Son of Rome</i> received mixed reviews. Aggregating review websites <a href="/wiki/GameRankings" title="GameRankings">GameRankings</a> and <a href="/wiki/Metacritic" title="Metacritic">Metacritic</a> gave the Xbox One version 64.30% and 60/100<sup id="cite_ref-GRXONE_10-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GRXONE-10"><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-MCXONE_12-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-MCXONE-12"><span>[</span>12<span>]</span></a></sup> and the Microsoft Windows version 62.40% and 58/100.<sup id="cite_ref-GRPC_11-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GRPC-11"><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-MCPC_13-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-MCPC-13"><span>[</span>13<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Electronic_Gaming_Monthly" title="Electronic Gaming Monthly">Electronic Gaming Monthly</a> gave the game a 7.5/10, praising the visuals but criticized the repetitive combat.<sup id="cite_ref-EGM_15-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-EGM-15"><span>[</span>15<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/GameSpot" title="GameSpot">GameSpot</a> was more critical on the game by giving it a 4/10, praising the great visuals and vocal performances, but criticizing the "shallow and repetitive combat", linear path, and multiplayer.<sup id="cite_ref-GSpot_17-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GSpot-17"><span>[</span>17<span>]</span></a></sup> Hex from <a href="/wiki/Good_Game" title="Good Game">Good Game</a> gave the game 8.5/10 saying that "the voice acting and mocap is all top-notch, with beautiful, stately dialogue".<sup id="cite_ref-21" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-21"><span>[</span>21<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/GameZone" title="GameZone">GameZone</a>'s Mike Splechta gave it a 7.5/10, stating "Sure, Ryse: Son of Rome is a gorgeous game, possibly the best looking Xbox One launch game despite its sub-1080p resolution."<sup id="cite_ref-GameZone_18-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GameZone-18"><span>[</span>18<span>]</span></a></sup> Emanuel Maiberg from <a href="/wiki/PC_Gamer" title="PC Gamer">PC Gamer</a> gave the game a 57/100, praising the character's animations, graphics and combat, but criticized the repetitive nature of the game.<sup id="cite_ref-PCGamer_20-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-PCGamer-20"><span>[</span>20<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
